BR Properties, BTG Pactual Agree to Merge Real Estate Assets

-- B y   A d r i a n a   B r a s i l e i r o
-- 
2011-09-14T22:20:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/br-properties-btg-pactual-agree-to-merge-real-estate-assets.html
Banco BTG Pactual SA, whose chief
executive officer is billionaire  Andre Esteves , and  BR
Properties SA (BRPR3)  agreed to merge their real-estate assets in an
all-share transaction.   BR Properties, a Brazilian property developer, will
incorporate the real estate assets of BTG and the bankâ€™s WTorre
Properties SA unit, BTG said in an e-mailed statement today.  In the new merged company, BR Properties shareholders will
have 58.1 percent of the total capital, while BTG will have 30.8
percent, according to the statement. WTorre will have 8.4
percent and the remaining 2.7 percent stake will be held by
other investors, BTG said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
